# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# |<----  Using a maximum of 50 characters  ---->|

# --- BODY (explain WHY, not WHAT — imperative present tense) ---
# |<----   Try to limit each line to 72 characters   ---->|

# --- FOOTER (Breaking Changes / closes #issue) ---

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TYPE must be one of:
#   feat     – new feature
#   fix      – bug fix
#   docs     – documentation only
#   style    – formatting, missing semicolons, etc. (no logic change)
#   refactor – code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   test     – adding or correcting tests
#   chore    – build process, tooling, maintenance
#
# SCOPE is optional — anything specifying the place of the change
#   e.g. feat(deploy-vm): ...
#
# SUBJECT rules:
#   - imperative, present tense: "add" not "added"/"adds"
#   - no capitalised first letter
#   - no dot (.) at the end
#
# BODY rules:
#   - explain motivation and contrast with previous behaviour
#   - imperative present tense
#
# FOOTER rules:
#   - note Breaking Changes: "BREAKING CHANGE: <description>"
#   - reference closed issues: "Closes #123"
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------